{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]Upon the Blue Ridge Mountains, there I'll take my stand.
[C]Upon the Blue Ridge Mountains,[C7]   [F]there I'll take my [C]stand.
A [F]rifle on my shoulder,
Six [C]shooter in my hand;
Lord, Lord, I've been all ar[G]ound this [C]world.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
[C]Lulu, my Lulu come and open the door.
[C]Lulu, my Lulu c[C7]ome and open [F]the [C]door.
Be[F]fore I have to walk on in
With my old f[C]orty-four.
Lord, Lord, I've been all ar[G]ound this [C]world.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
[C]Mama and Papa, little sister makes three.
[C]Mama and Papa, [C7]little [F]sister makes [C]three.
[F]They're comin' in the mornin';
That's the [C]last you'll see of me.
Lord, Lord, I've been all ar[G]ound this [C]world.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
[C]Hang me, oh, hang me, so I'll be dead and gone.
Hang me, [C7]oh, hang me, so [F]I'll be dead and [C]gone.
[F]I wouldn't mind your hangin' boys,
But you [C]wait in jail so long.
Lord, Lord, I've been all ar[G]ound this [C]world.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 5}
[C]Upon the Blue Ridge Mountains, there I'll take my stand.
Upon the Blue Ridge [C7]Mountains, [F]there I'll take my [C]stand.
[F]A rifle on my shoulder,
Six [C]shooter in my hand;
Lord, Lord, I've been all [G]around this [C]world.
{end_of_verse}
